## Disaster recovery

Brief version (full procedure in the
[safety-critical workflow](safety-critical.md)):

1. Provision a fresh PG instance and run `mtix migrate` against it.
2. From a clone of the repo, run `mtix import .mtix/tasks.json --to-postgres`
   to seed the new instance from the most recent snapshot.
3. Replay any post-snapshot audit log entries from your PG backups (if
   available).
4. Update each developer's `MTIX_PG_DSN` to point at the new instance.

The committed `tasks.json` snapshots act as a coarse-grained recovery
point. For finer granularity (per-mutation audit trail, point-in-time
restore), see the safety-critical workflow.

